This is really, really good. Three normal dudes thrust into a position of nearly absolute power by complete accident is a really compelling concept, and you really pulled off the . I love this.

A particular thing I'd like to praise is the tone. Obviously the second note isn't what we'd usually call clinical, and I think that really works. Clinical tone on this site is effective, imo, because of the contrast of the impossible and the mundane; it emphasizes that this kind of stuff is normalized within the Foundation. I think that note gets across exactly the same feel in an entirely different way by replacing , which is something you don't see a lot.

(I'm also excited to see more Archon skips. They're sort of antithetical to the Foundation's whole Thing™ but I think they're really interesting to explore because of that.)

This contest has been great, a lot of things have come out of it that I really enjoyed, but I don't necessarily want to see take the 4000 spot. This is one of only a couple that I'd be unreservedly happy to see win.





